In his address to the United Nations General Assembly, President Donald J. Trump emphasized the importance of national sovereignty and the responsibility of governments to respect the interests of their own people. He argued that strong and independent nations are crucial for democracy and that sovereignty is a moral imperative. The President's National Security Strategy also highlights the significance of human rights in advancing American influence abroad and ensuring peace and prosperity. The Trump Administration has consistently used diplomacy, sanctions, and other tools to isolate states and leaders who violate human rights. President Trump believes in condemning human rights abuses and holding perpetrators accountable. He believes that if good people and nations do not confront evil, it will prevail.